headline: NYSE-parent ICE plans to launch battery metals derivatives this year
summary: Intercontinental Exchange plans to launch derivatives in battery metals cobalt and lithium spodumene in London later this year, an executive said on Tuesday.  "ICE are planning to launch battery raw materials this year, lithium and cobalt and spodumene will be the start of that."  A ICE spokesperson said the exchange was looking at adding contracts in lithium carbonate, lithium hydroxide, lithium spodumene and cobalt.
